# Writerdeck for reMarkable 1

Migration 2 Phase A (pure math/undo → `EditHelper`) shipped @ fork `a92ad2b`. Phase B/C handoff: [docs/editor-migration-2-to-cpp/todo-handoff-edit-helper-cpp.md](docs/editor-migration-2-to-cpp/todo-handoff-edit-helper-cpp.md).

## Audience and replies

The owner is a **designer with basic code skills**, not a professional developer. Unless they ask for depth: keep chat replies **terse**, in **plain layman’s prose**, and lead with what happened / what to do next. Avoid jargon dumps, long architecture digressions, and “what we didn’t do” lists. Save technical detail for commits, handoff docs, and when asked.

## Drivers

Document integrity is the absolute paramount driver — the owner's prose must survive as plain Markdown on disk. That outranks feature speed and polishing the typing tests. See [docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) § Document integrity, [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md), [docs/integrity-audit.md](docs/integrity-audit.md). Before inventing editor behavior, check how similar editors do it (CodeMirror, Qt `TextEdit`, Mac/Linux text fields) and prefer proven patterns.

## Verify before calling work done (mandatory — do not skip)

**Deploy success ≠ tested. curl/API 200 ≠ UI works.**

After `daemon/`, `build-keywriter.sh`, Lobby/QML (fork), or deploy-script changes:

### Phone browser UI (required for any `daemon/*.js` / embedded HTML/CSS change)

`curl` cannot catch ES module load failures — the page can show static `connecting...` with zero JS running.

1. Deploy (`deploy-rmkbd.sh`; ensure `systemctl start writerdeck` if service stopped)
2. **Load the page** at `http://$RM_HOST:8000/` (browser tools or real browser) — hard refresh if cached
3. Confirm **JavaScript actually ran**:
   - Notes list populated (not empty with only the static top bar)
   - Connection bar shows **Connected** or **Tablet offline** — not stuck on HTML default `connecting...`
   - PIN screen hidden when `pinDigits` is `none`
4. Spot-check changed UI (e.g. Sync setup modal, Save/Sync buttons)
5. If modules fail to load, fix before moving on (common: duplicate `export` in `connection.js`)

Cursor’s embedded browser must not count as a Lobby keyboard path (no WebSocket `hello` / ignored by User-Agent). Journal after Lobby up: `lobby presence phone=false` is expected when only Cursor tabs are connected — see [docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) §34.

### Tablet / server (required for all deploys)

1. Rebuild Writerdeck if QML/C++ changed → push fork if needed → `git push` (this repo) → `fetch-keywriter-dist.sh` → `deploy-keywriter.sh -b`
2. SSH → `journalctl -u writerdeck -n 30` — fail on QML parse errors or instant `editor process exited`
3. `bash scripts/test-edit-session.sh` after Writerdeck/QML deploy
4. `bash scripts/test-keyboard-harness.sh --fast` after QML arrow, selection, or `handleKey` changes (see `docs/decisions.md` **Typing-test strategy is failing** and §13). Green is a score for those checks, not proof basic editing works. Done means all checks passed (`--list` count). Basic editing set: `-t critical --fast` → **57/57/0**. Update [milestone-runs.md](docs/editor-testing/milestone-runs.md) after every full run. While iterating keyboard bugs, list all failures before deploying — at most one Writerdeck binary deploy per session unless QML fails to launch (see `docs/editor-testing/todo.md`, `docs/lessons.md`).
5. `bash scripts/test-lobby-keyboard.sh` after Lobby, `handleHome`, or `lobbyFocus` changes (see `docs/decisions.md` #15)

Run all applicable steps every time without being asked. Do not declare done with known gaps ("not yet on tablet", "should work"). Do not run edit-session and the typing-test script in parallel.

## Time budget while debugging

No built-in task timer. Estimate elapsed time from message timestamps and shell command durations (deploy logs, typing-test runs).

After about 20 minutes on one task without a clear finish, stop implementing. Report to the user: what you tried, what consumed time, whether you used the smallest check first ([lessons.md](docs/lessons.md)), and what you would do next. Ask before another full deploy-and-test cycle. Keyboard test iteration: one run to list failures, batch fixes, one Writerdeck deploy — not push/deploy per case.

Do not `pkill -f /home/root/Writerdeck` (matches Writerdeck-server). On-device naming: `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/decisions.md` #29.

## Observation (typing bug demos)

When the user says they observed a bug, finished observing, or asks you to look at an observation: immediately fetch it from the tablet on the LAN. Do not ask them to download or paste a file.

```bash
source scripts/_env.sh
curl -s "http://$RM_HOST:8000/api/observe/export"
```

Or `bash scripts/fetch-observation.sh` (writes `docs/recon/last-observation.json`). Status: `GET /api/observe/status` (`ready: true` when a stop is waiting). Phone path only — not USB-on-tablet keys.

The Observe button is hidden unless `settings.observe` is true. Enable for this device:

```bash
curl -s -X POST "http://$RM_HOST:8000/api/settings" -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"observe":true}'
```

## Constraints

- No jailbreak; preserve OTA (over-the-air updates) → avoid Toltec
- Static Go only: `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm GOARM=7`
- Markdown save format
- Cross-compile Writerdeck-server on Mac; never local `docker build` for Writerdeck — GitHub Actions + `fetch-keywriter-dist.sh`
- Do not grow new editor behavior in `build-keywriter.sh` — edit the fork ([docs/decisions.md](docs/decisions.md) §4)

## Dev setup

Secrets: `secrets/remarkable.local.env`; scripts source `scripts/_env.sh` for `RM_HOST`.

**Daemon:** `deploy-rmkbd.sh` → `systemctl restart writerdeck`. Verify APIs **and** load the phone UI (see above) — not `curl` alone.

**Writerdeck:** editor changes in Writerdeck-keywriter → push fork → this repo’s CI (or wait for rebuild) → `fetch-keywriter-dist.sh` → `deploy-keywriter.sh -b`. Relaunch Writerdeck after binary deploy (server restart alone is not enough). Then `bash scripts/test-edit-session.sh`; `bash scripts/test-lobby-keyboard.sh` after Lobby/`handleHome` QML; `bash scripts/test-keyboard-harness.sh` when keyboard/selection QML changed.

GitHub token: browser `localStorage ghToken` + tablet RAM via `POST /api/sync/token`; after restart WebSocket `needtoken` triggers auto-repost. Logs: `journalctl -u writerdeck.service` — token restore shows `sync reconcile (token)` after `client connected` (see `docs/server-sync-implementation.md`).

## Documentation

Write like John Gruber: complete sentences, direct, minimal formatting — almost no bold, no emoji, no `Status: built` scaffolding. Prose over bullet dumps; use tables only when the data is inherently tabular (e.g. browser vs tablet), not as default structure. Short cross-links at the top, not boilerplate on every file. Avoid process slang; keep real tech names — [docs/jargon-to-avoid.md](docs/jargon-to-avoid.md).

Terse and forward-looking. Keep durable operational commands and lessons (what worked, what didn't, why). Prune settled history, chatty narration, and decisions that won't help anyone extending the project later. When in doubt, keep — but don't pad.

Standing docs only: `TODO.md`, `DONE.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/decisions.md`, `docs/lessons.md`. How → architecture; why → decisions; gotchas → lessons. No new summary markdown files. Prune dead scripts/files when paths close; grep references first.

## Encoding

Executable/device files (`.sh`, `.service`, `.go`, `.yml`, Dockerfile): ASCII-only + LF, no BOM. Markdown `.md`: Unicode OK. Before committing scripts: grep for `[^\x00-\x7F]` — must be empty for `.sh`/`.ps1`.
